wdi-AG.LND.ARBL.HA.def: Arable land (in hectares) includes land defined by the FAO as land under temporary crops (double-cropped areas are counted once), temporary meadows for mowing or for pasture, land under market or kitchen gardens, and land temporarily fallow. Land abandoned as a result of shifting cultivation is excluded.
wdi-AG.LND.ARBL.HA.name: Arable land
wdi-AG.LND.ARBL.HA.source: Food and Agriculture Organization, electronic files and web site.
